    <h1>Assignment &amp; State</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Abelson &amp; Sussman · 1996 · <a href="https://mitp-content-server.mit.edu/books/content/sectbyfn/books_pres_0/6515/sicp.zip/full-text/book/book-Z-H-20.html#%_sec_3.1">SICP §3.1</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><code>set!</code> introduces time into the model. Once variables can change, substitution breaks down. Objects with local state model real-world entities but sacrifice referential transparency.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Bank account state diagram -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 420 140" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
